HEADWORD: Ciceronianism
<hw>Cic`e*ro"ni*an*ism</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>Imitation
of, or resemblance to, the style or action Cicero; a Ciceronian phrase
or expression.</def> ⟦ldquo⟧Great study in <xex>Ciceronianism</xex>, the
chief abuse of Oxford.⟦rdquo⟧ <rj><au>Sir P. Sidney.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

